r\")","+}","+","+// logSink returns the writer to which logs should be sent, pointing the","+// standard library's default logger at it on first call. It returns nil if","+// syslog logging was not requested or the syslog daemon is unreachable.","+var logSink = sync.OnceValue(func() io.Writer {","+\tif !useSyslog {","+\t\treturn nil","+\t}","+\tw, err := syslog.New(syslog.LOG_DAEMON|syslog.LOG_INFO, \"tailscaled\")","+\tif err != nil {","+\t\tlog.Printf(\"syslog: connecting to syslog daemon failed; continuing to log to stderr: %v\", err)","+\t\treturn nil","+\t}","+\tlog.SetFlags(0) // syslog records its own timestamps","+\tlog.SetOutput(w)","+\treturn w","+})"],"additions":47,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"logpolicy/logpolicy.go","lines":["@@ -546,7 +546,18 @@ func (opts Options) init(disableLogging bool) (*logtail.Config, *Policy) {"," \t\t// anyway, no need to add one."," \t\tlflags = 0"," \t}","-\tconsole := log.New(stderrWriter{}, \"\", lflags)","+\tvar conWriter io.Writer = stderrWriter{}","+\tif buildfeatures.HasSyslog {","+\t\tif f, ok := feature.HookLogSink.GetOk(); ok {","+\t\t\tif w := f(); w != nil {","+\t\t\t\t// Logs are being redirected elsewhere (e.g. to syslog,","+\t\t\t\t// which records its own timestamps).","+\t\t\t\tconWriter = w","+\t\t\t\tlflags = 0","+\t\t\t}","+\t\t}","+\t}","+\tconsole := log.New(conWriter, \"\", lflags)"," "," \tvar earlyErrBuf bytes.Buffer"," \tearlyLogf := func(format string, a ...any) {",""],"additions":12,"deletions":1,"truncated":false}],"additions":137,"deletions":2,"truncated":false,"file_count":10},"error":null,"fetched_at":"2026-07-18T09:24:40.797433+00:00"}